article.description: American U. 66, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 45
article.headline: American U. 66, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 45
article.linkText: American U. 66, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 45
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. (AP) -- Travis Lay scored a game-high 17 points and grabbed 7 rebounds, and American defeated Mount St. Mary's 66-45 Monday night. Lay made 7 of 7 free throws and landed 5 of 8 from the field. Although the Eagles only shot 39 percent, they methodically played offense and lock-down defense, holding Mount St. Mary's to 31.4 percent in shooting. Garrison Carr had 12 points and Brian Gilmore and Constantin Motnii contributed 10 points each for American (4-3). Jeremy Goode scored a team-high 10 points for Mount St. Mary's (0-4). Derrick Mercer added seven assists and six rebounds.
